# AI Promptbook v2 – Cursor Rules
# Loaded automatically by the Cursor AI editor

## Project identity
You are working on **AI Promptbook v2** – a native desktop app for managing AI agent instructions, prompts, and project templates. Stack: React 19 + TypeScript + Vite + Tauri 2 (Rust backend).

## Architecture rules

### File organisation
- `src/features/<name>/` – one folder per page/route
- `src/ui/` – shared layout, components, theme
- `src/services/` – Tauri IPC and async operations
- `src/state/` – Zustand stores
- `src/domain/` – pure types and utilities
- `src-tauri/src/lib.rs` – Rust Tauri commands

### TypeScript / React rules
- Functional components and hooks only; no class components
- Explicit TypeScript types on all parameters and return values; no `any`
- Shared mutable state lives in a Zustand store, never prop-drilled
- File I/O exclusively through `@tauri-apps/plugin-fs`; never browser storage APIs
- GitHub tokens must always be encrypted via `src/services/cryptoService.ts`
- Validate with `tsc --noEmit` after every significant change

### Rust rules
- All `clippy` warnings must be resolved
- Tauri commands return `Result<T, String>`
- Cryptographic operations stay in `src-tauri/src/lib.rs`

## Common task patterns

### New feature page
```
src/features/<name>/<Name>Page.tsx   ← main component
src/routes.tsx                        ← add route entry
src/ui/layouts/AppShell.tsx          ← add nav link
```

### Tauri IPC call
```ts
import { invoke } from '@tauri-apps/api/core';
const data = await invoke<ReturnType>('rust_command', { arg });
```

### File read/write
```ts
import { readTextFile, writeTextFile, BaseDirectory } from '@tauri-apps/plugin-fs';
```

## Hard constraints
- NEVER use localStorage / sessionStorage / indexedDB
- NEVER expose a GitHub PAT in plain text
- NEVER skip Tauri capability permissions in `src-tauri/capabilities/`
- NEVER add a dependency without a clear justification in the PR description
